###How to fix the Common Vulnerabilities issue of CVE-2019-10081 in nginx web server and which owasp top 10 web 2021 category this issue belong to ?
CVE-2019-10081 is a vulnerability in the nginx web server that allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code on the affected system. The vulnerability is caused by a flaw in the way that nginx handles HTTP requests with the chunked transfer encoding.

To fix this vulnerability, you should upgrade your nginx web server to a version that includes a patch for CVE-2019-10081. You can find the latest version of nginx at the nginx website.

This vulnerability belongs to the OWASP Top 10 2021 category of Injection. Injection flaws, such as CVE-2019-10081, occur when unvalidated or malicious data is sent to an interpreter as part of a command or query. The attacker's hostile data can trick the interpreter into executing unintended commands or accessing data without proper authorization.

Here are some additional steps you can take to protect your nginx web server from attack:

* Use a strong password for your nginx web server.
* Enable HTTP authentication for your nginx web server.
* Keep your nginx web server up to date with the latest security patches.
* Use a firewall to restrict access to your nginx web server.
* Use a web application firewall (WAF) to protect your nginx web server from common attacks.
